OL,3,CFlat 'grossly overcrowded' ahead of
OL,4,Cfatal e-bike fire, court told
OL,6,FThe blaze was started accidentally by
OL,7,Fa faulty lithium ion e-bike battery
OL,8,Fthat was charging at the time, the
OL,9,FLondon Fire Brigade have said.
OL,11,FInvestigations are still ongoing and a
OL,12,Fcivil matter has already been lodged.
OL,14,FBegum, whose name was on the licence,
OL,15,Fhas pleaded guilty to six offences
OL,16,Fincluding knowingly permitting
OL,17,Funlicensed occupation, four counts of
OL,18,Ffailing to comply with licence
OL,19,Fconditions and failing to comply with
OL,20,Fthe requirements of a licence notice.
