OL,3,CFlat 'grossly overcrowded' ahead of
OL,4,Cfatal e-bike fire, court told
OL,6,FRahman, who collected the rent and was
OL,7,Fthe person responsible for the
OL,8,Fproperty, has pleaded guilty to one
OL,9,Fcount of each of these three offences.
OL,11,FThey failed to allow regular
OL,12,Finspections, did not have a current
OL,13,Fgas certificate and did not produce
OL,14,Fthe documents required of them as the
OL,15,Fcontroller or manager of a the
OL,16,Fproperty.
OL,18,FAfter the fire, Rahman told a liaison
OL,19,Fofficer that he rented the flat to two
OL,20,Fpeople and he did not know who the
OL,21,Fothers were.
